This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with stereo matching, which is a fundamental problem in computer vision. The paper also proposes a new framework for cost aggregation, which is a key step in stereo matching. 

The paper also involves optimization and regularization, which are common techniques in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). 

The paper may also be relevant to Graphics (cs.GR) as stereo matching is important in 3D graphics and computer-generated imagery. 

Finally, the paper may be relevant to Multimedia (cs.MM) as stereo matching is important in video processing and 3D reconstruction, which are common topics in multimedia research.
